Guide to the Irving Godt Papers

                    <date>1952-2002 </date>
                    <lb/>(Bulk

author.value: Finding aid prepared by Laura Zeccardi. Series VII processed by Catriona Schlosser.

creation.value:
This finding aid was produced using the Archivists' Toolkit
                <date>2013-01-17T12:15-0500</date>

abstract.label: Abstract
abstract.value: The Papers of Irving Godt comprise the pedagogical and research works of a music professor who taught at both universities and liberal arts colleges during his career. Included are his correspondence with colleagues and publishers, lecture notes and lesson plans, and original works of music and fiction.

p.value:
The first 35 boxes of this collection are in
                <extref ns2:href="http://www.nyu.edu/library/bobst/research/arch/godt.htm">
                    <archref> off-site storage</archref> </extref>, and you must contact the repository for access.

Published citations should take the following form: 
                <lb/>
                <lb/>Identification of item, date (if known); The Irving Godt Papers; MC 206; box number; folder number; 
                <address>
                    <addressline>New York University ;</addressline>
                    <addressline>New York University</addressline>
                </address>

<list>
                    <item>Rakhonen, Carl. "In memoriam: Irving Godt, 1923-2006." Allegheny Chapter of the American Musicological Society, Recent Chapter News. Found online at: http://www.people.iup.edu/rahkonen/AllegAMS/recentnews.htm.</item>
                </list>

Series VII of this collection is an accretion that consists of his research on 18th-century composer Marianna Martines. The bulk of materials contained in this series include reproductions of Martines musical scores; reproductions of letters and writings from Martines; drafts of journal articles and books on the composer; and correspondence with publishers, advisors, colleagues and archivists.
